==================================
https://suckless.org/coding_style/
==================================

* Function name and argument list on next line. This allows to grep for function
  names simply using grep ^functionname(.
* Functions not used outside translation unit should be declared and defined
  static.
* Keep lines to reasonable length (max 79 characters).

I don't really like a lot of these (ie. third bullet) -- probably because most
of the points aren't expanded upon at all. I'm really glad the first point was
explained because it makes a fair bit of sense.

Most other style guides don't seem to mention use of `static`, which is nice
they included this

